## Description & highlights

- `description`: 2–3 short, natural paragraphs (`\n\n` between). Premium but calm tone — no "шикарная", "люкс", "богатая", "топовая", "идеальная". No canned corporate phrasing. Vary wording across products, don't reuse the same sentences.
- `highlights`: array of 3–4 short factual bullet points (material, key construction detail, strap/closure, hardware). Only real facts — never invent a detail that isn't in the photos/spec.
- Don't fabricate facts (e.g. a detachable strap) if it isn't visible/confirmed.

## Leather terminology

The shop only carries genuine leather — no eco-leather, no vague hedging.

- Always say **"кожа"** (RU) — never plain "натуральная кожа", never "экокожа"/"искусственная кожа".
- Suede: "замша".
- English `material` facet field: use "Leather" (e.g. `"Woven Texture Base + Leather Trim"`, `"Premium Leather"`).

## Specs table

- `"Страна производства"`: use the real country if known (usually `"Италия"`); if unknown, use `"Уточняется по бирке/поставщику"` — never leave it out or just say `"Уточняется"`.
- **Important UI quirk**: `getVisibleProductSpecs` in `src/lib/product-i18n.ts` hides any spec row labeled exactly `"Материал"` from the UI. If a product needs a *visible* material line in the specs table, label it `"Кожа"` (or another non-hidden label), not `"Материал"`.
- Keep existing label conventions (Размер, Ручки, Ремень, Пряжка, Отделение, Карманы, Застёжка, Фурнитура, Подкладка, Доставка).

## Image/product mechanics (recap)

- Image naming: `{color}-front.png`, `-back.png`, `-side.png`, `-inside.png`, `-open.png`, `-set.png`, `-front-alt.png`.
- `galleryFit: "contain"` for wide/structured photos so they don't get cropped on cards.
- Standard defaults: `brandSlug: "luma-atelier"`, `price: 1600`, `status: "in_stock"`, `isNew: true`.
